          <actionDate>2018-03-14</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Mass Violence Prevention Reform Act</b></p> <p>This bill makes it unlawful to transfer or receive an assault rifle during the 60-day period following enactment. An individual who knowingly violates the prohibition is subject to criminal penalties.</p> <p>During the 60-day moratorium, the Department of Health and Human Services, the Federal Bureau of Investigation, and the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives must make recommendations to Congress: (1) on a legal definition of &quot;assault weapon&quot; and (2) on other policies related to firearms that are in the interest of public health. </p>]]></text>
